<DATELINE>MIAMI BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jimmy ``The Greek'' Snyder, fired as a
CBS sports commentator earlier this year, says he's been ``hiding''
in a posh hotel since then. To add to his troubles, he's back in
the hospital for chest pains.
   The 70-year-old oddsmaker was in good condition and undergoing
tests and observation, Miami Heart Institute spokeswoman Esther
Saporito said Thursday.
   Snyder, dismissed from ``NFL Today'' in January because of his
controversial remarks about black athletes, said he woke up in his
hotel room here Wednesday with chest pains.
   ``I don't take any chances, the sooner they can do something for
you the better,'' he said from his hospital bed. ``They (doctors)
are just looking to see what they find.''
   Snyder was hospitalized last July at Duke Medical Center in
Durham, N.C., where examinations disclosed that an artery to his
heart was blocked, and again shortly after his firing. Afterward,
Snyder took up residence alone at the posh, oceanfront Alexander
Hotel on Miami Beach.
   ``I've been hiding there for 2{ months and then this had to
happen,'' said Snyder, adding that he didn't feel ``too good right
now.''
