<HEAD>Barbara Bush Stumps Ohio On Husband's Behalf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Barbara Bush wound up a two-day campaign
visit to Ohio on behalf of her husband, Vice President George Bush,
in advance of Ohio's May 3 primaries.
   Mrs. Bush on Thursday visited Fairborn, where she endorsed the
re-election campaign of Republican U.S. Rep. Michael DeWine, and
then went on to Chillicothe, Columbus and Lancaster.
