with stops in Cincinnati, Dayton, Lebanon and Middletown. She said
she is relieved that her husband no longer faces a strong challenge
for the Republican nomination for president.
   ``We thought we'd be fighting coming into Ohio,'' Mrs. Bush
said. ``How sweet it is to pull the party together. This is the
time to unify and get going.''
