<HEAD>Proxmire Proud Of Wisconsin Voters' Support For Jackson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. William Proxmire says he has never been
prouder of Wisconsin than when it gave Jesse Jackson a strong
second-place finish in the state's April 5 presidential primary.
   ``A black man won 23 percent of the vote of whites voting in the
Democratic primary,'' Proxmire, D-Wis., said in a Senate speech
