They voted for a black man as president of the United States. I've
never been prouder of my state.''
   Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis won the primary with 48
percent of the vote, while Jackson was second with 28 percent.
   Proxmire said he based his estimate of the white vote for
Jackson on published results of exit polling outside voting places.
