<HEAD>April Showers and Spring Snow Fall on California, Nevada</HEAD>
<HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Spring snow blanketed mountains in Southern California today
while April showers dampened their lower elevations, but fair skies
prevailed across much of the rest of the nation.
   A winter storm warning for up to 7 to 14 inches of snow at the
higher reaches of Southern California's mountains was in effect
today, with up to 2 inches of rain for the lower reaches, and up to
an inch of rain on the coast.
   Showers and a few thunderstorms ranged over west Texas, and a
wave of cold air brought showers and scattered, light snow to the
upper Great Lakes and showers to the mid- and northern Atlantic
Coast.
   There were also scattered showers over Tennessee and southern
Missouri.
   Freezing temperatures prevailed early today from North Dakota
and eastern South Dakota to Michigan, and a freeze advisory was
posted for central and northwestern Indiana.
   Today's national weather forecast called for rain scattered from
the upper Ohio Valley into New England, with scattered snow across
eastern upper Michigan and northeast lower Michigan from northeast
Ohio through northwest Pennsylvania, into parts of western New York
state; showers and a few thunderstorms over the southern valleys of
California into the southern inter-mountain region.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 50s or 60s across
much of the nation; in the 40s from the upper Great Lakes into the
Ohio Valley and New England; in the 30s over Michigan and the
shores of the eastern Great Lakes; in the 70s across the Rockies,
western Texas and southern Oklahoma into the south-eastern states
and much of Florida; in the low to mid 80s across southern and
southeast Texas into the central Gulf Coast.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 23
degrees at Marquette, Mich., and Warroad, Minn., to 73 degrees at
Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 39 cloudy; Buffalo 35 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 59 fair; Cincinnati 39 fair; Cleveland 40
partly cloudy; Detroit 37 cloudy; Miami 63 fair; New York 41
cloudy; Philadelphia 40 showery; Pittsburgh 39 partly cloudy;
Portland, Maine 38 cloudy; Washington 45 thunderstorms.
   _Central: Bismarck 24 fair; Chicago 38 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth
66 cloudy; Denver 44 fair; Des Moines 37 fair; Indianapolis 38
fair; Kansas City 41 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 36 fair; Nashville
54 partly cloudy; New Orleans 57 foggy; St. Louis 44 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 48 fair; Anchorage 35 cloudy; Las Vegas 55
cloudy; Los Angeles 52 cloudy; Phoenix 74 partly cloudy; Salt Lake
City 50 cloudy; San Diego 52 rain; San Francisco 54 cloudy; Seattle
51 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 45 cloudy; Toronto 32 partly cloudy.
