<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Gadhafi-Bush 1stLd-Writethru a0530 04-15 0208</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Gadhafi-Bush, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0530,210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gadhafi Says Bush Would Be Best President</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Recasts lead; also subs 2 grafs for last graf to add detail</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Libyan leader Moammar Gadhafi says Vice
President George Bush is his choice to succeed President Reagan
``because he has suffered from the irrationality of Reagan ... and
he would sort of make up for it.''
   Gadhafi, in a taped interview aired today on NBC-TV's ``Today''
show, said Libyan relations with the United States could improve,
``but with Reagan it is impossible.''
   ``Undoubtedly, relations will improve and any new elected
president would not be as crazy as Reagan,'' he continued, speaking
in Arabic through an interpreter.
   He was then asked about the U.S. presidential contest: ``Do you
see a man there that you admire most and you would like to see to
be president of the United States?''
   Gadhafi responded: ``I think that Mr. Bush who has worked with
Reagan and who has suffered from the irrationality of Reagan and
foolishness and he was an eyewitness of the American damage and
American loss in the period of Reagan. So he would be a better
president because he has suffered with Reagan and he would sort of
make up for it.''
</TEXT>
