<HEAD>Loh Chosen to Head Aeronautical Systems Division</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan has nominated Maj. Gen. John
M. Loh for promotion to lieutenant general and assignment as
commander of the Air Force Aeronautical Systems Division, the
Pentagon said Friday.
   Assuming he is confirmed by the Senate, the 50-year-old Loh will
replace Gen. William E. Thurman, who will retire Aug. 1 after 34
years of active-duty service. Thurman, 56, of Hodgenville, Ky., has
headed the Aeronautical Systems Division since June 1986.
   Loh, a native of Washington, D.C., now is vice commander of the
division, which is part of the Air Force Systems Command and
responsible for developing and buying new aircraft.
