<DOCNO> AP880415-0119 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-04-15-88 1312EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--Reagan-Safety     04-15 0079</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Reagan-Safety,70</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Reappoints Burnett to Head Transportation Safety Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan announced Friday he is
reappointing James Burnett to a two-year term as chairman of the
National Transportation Safety Board.
   Burnett has been a member of the board since 1981 and became
chairman in 1982. Before joining the board he was a juvenile judge
in Van Buren, Ark., a city judge in Damascus, Ark., and a special
associate justice of the Arkansas Supreme Court.
