<HEAD>World War II Submarine Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KIEL, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Divers have discovered a Nazi U-boat
submerged inside a partially destroyed submarine pen near Kiel,
city officials said Friday.
   Several months ago, long-time residents told city officials they
recalled there had been a submarine inside the giant concrete
U-boat bunker, and divers were hired to search for the vessel
earlier this month.
   Allied warplanes heavily bombed U-boat pens in northern Germany
during World War II.
   The submarine pen, on the east side of the Baltic Sea inlet
where Kiel is located, was originally 198 feet wide and 561 feet
long, city officials say.
   Some people want the pen preserved as a memorial, but city
planners want to clear the area to develop the harbor.
