<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Brazil-Shooting     04-15 0175</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brazil-Shooting,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Popular Singer Shoots Girlfriend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Brazilian singer and composer Nelson
Ned shot and wounded his girlfriend, apparently after a lovers'
quarrel, police said Friday.
   The 40-year-old singer is famous for his romantic ballads, many
of which he sings in Spanish. He is widely popular among Latin
American communities in Florida and New York.
   Ned shot Maria Aparecida Rodrigues, 32, wounding her in the
chest on Sunday, said police inspector Adolpho de Andrade Rebello.
Ms. Rodrigues, who has lived with Ned for the past eight years, was
``out of danger'' after being treated, he said.
   Rebello said police wanted to question Ned to determine whether
the shooting was accidental or premeditated.
   He said the singer was in Dallas, according to his lawyer.
   ``But we also have information he may be in Rio de Janeiro or
hiding somewhere in Sao Paulo.''
   The police inspector said Ned could be sentenced to up one year
in prison if the shooting was accidental and up to 20 years if it
was attempted homicide.
