<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Pakistan-Rockets     04-15 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Pakistan-Rockets,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rockets Explode At Devastated Ammo Dump; Five Hurt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A dozen rockets went off Friday at a
smoldering ammunition dump that exploded five days earlier, the
Defense Ministry said. Five people were injured in the latest
blasts.
   High temperatures rekindled fires at the devastated ammunition
dump, detonating twelve rockets, the official Pakistan News Agency
quoted a Defense Ministry spokesman as saying.
   Five people were injured in surrounding areas, the news agency
said.
   The ammunition dump at Ojdri army camp is between the twin
cities of Islamabad and Rawalpindi.
   The explosion on Sunday detonated rockets, missiles and other
weapons, killing at least 96 people, wounding more than 1,000
others and showering the cities with debris.
   President Mohammed Zia ul-Haq has said that sabotage caused
Sunday's blast, but he has not said which group is responsible.
   The army has been blowing up unexploded projectiles outside
Islamabad.
   Authorities urged people to stay indoors after Friday's rocket
blasts.
</TEXT>
