on ethical questions involving the emerging technique.
   The first reported use of the experimental procedure was in
January when surgeons in Mexico City said they had injected tissue
from a miscarried fetus into the brains of two Parkinson's
sufferers. The researchers said the results were promising.
   Researchers in Sweden also have reported using a similar
technique, but there have been no documented instances of it being
done on humans in the United States.

