Chicago Mercantile Exchange.
   Live cattle were .05 cent to .25 cent lower with April at 73.57
cents a pound; feeder cattle were .02 cent to .20 cent lower with
April at 79.45 cents a pound; hogs were unchanged to .27 cent lower
with April at 44.75 cents a pound; frozen pork bellies were .17
cent lower to .90 cent higher with May at 51.90 cents a pound.
   Livestock and meat futures settled mostly higher on Thursday.
