<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some of the major business events and economic events
scheduled for the coming week (some dates are tentative):
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>MONDAY, April 18</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   WASHINGTON _ The Federal Reserve is to report on the percentage
of factory capacity in use during March; release time uncertain.
   DETROIT _ Chrysler Corp. and the United Auto Workers union are
scheduled to begin negotiations on a new contract.
   WASHINGTON _ The Supreme Court issues orders today, possibly
announces decisions on Tuesday and hears arguments today, Tuesday
and Wednesday.
   HOUSTON _ Today is the new deadline for holders of First City
Bancorporation of Texas Inc. debt to tender their securities for a
loss under a revised federally assisted bailout. The deadline has
been extended six times.
</TEXT>
