<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Comsat     04-15 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Comsat,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Comsat Revenues Up Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communications Satellite Corp. on Friday
reported a 68 percent jump in its first quarter profit over a year
ago.
   Net income for the three months ended March 31 totaled $14.3
million, or 77 cents a share, compared with earnings of $8.5
million, or 44 cents, in 1987.
   Revenue totaled $84.1 million vs. $80.7 million. Operating
income, however, fell from $22.9 million to $18.4 million, the
company said.
   The jump in revenue was attributed largely to the acquisition of
full ownership in Comsat Video Enterprises Inc., which was added to
the company in the second quarter of last year.
   This was partially offset, though, by a decline in revenue from
Intelsat Satellite Services. While international business was up,
revenue declined because of rate reductions to customers under
long-term contracts, Comsat reported.
   Comsat provides international, domestic and maritime
communications facilities via satellite and researches
communications techniques.
</TEXT>
